<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph box="[966,1875,652,1017]" pageId="16" pageNumber="269" type="mainText">
Small shrubs. Flowers bisexual, sometimes pistillate, solitary or 2-3 together, in spicate inflorescences; perianth urceolate, with 5 inflexed lobes; fruiting perianth slightly accrescent, membranous, without appendages; stamens 5; stigmas 2. Pericarp free; seeds horizontal; embryo horseshoe-shaped; radicle centrifugal; perisperm sparse or absent. Four spp., Africa. Possibly not generically distinct from 
<taxonomicName class="Hydrozoa" family="Abylidae" genus="Bassia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonophorae" pageId="16" pageNumber="269" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Bassia</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
